* littext.pkg -- installation manifest for the littext package
*
* This file is read by Stata's net command when a user runs
*
*     net install littext
*
* Every f line below declares one file that net install will copy into
* the user's PLUS adopath. Comment lines begin with an asterisk at
* column 1; no other comment syntax is recognised by the manifest
* grammar.
*
v 3
d littext: automated construct discovery and relationship inference from academic text
d
d {bf:littext} extracts candidate construct relationships from a corpus
d of academic text (titles, abstracts, full texts). It produces three
d Stata frames -- lt_constructs, lt_relations, lt_diag -- holding the
d extracted constructs, candidate relationships with confidence scores
d and evidence sentences, and per-document diagnostics. A companion
d {bf:littext graph} command produces ten visualisation types (five
d Stata-native, five matplotlib).
d
d The pipeline combines spaCy noun-chunk extraction, sentence-
d transformer embeddings, HDBSCAN synonym clustering, normalised
d pointwise mutual information for relationship candidacy, and a
d six-pattern dependency-arc matcher for relationship valence.
d
d Requires Stata 19 with Python integration configured. Required
d Python packages: spacy, sentence-transformers, hdbscan, scikit-learn,
d umap-learn, matplotlib, networkx, pandas, numpy. Optional package
d for the addsentiment option: vaderSentiment. Run {stata littext
d install, verbose} after installation to check the Python
d environment.
d
d Author: Nebojsa S. Davcik, EM Normandie Business School
d Support: davcik@live.com
d ORCID: 0000-0003-1041-8788
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260525
d
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
* Top-level Stata files: dispatchers, subcommand handlers, help, alias.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
f littext.ado
f littext.sthlp
f litt.ado
f litt.sthlp
f _littext_install.ado
f _littext_analyze.ado
f _littext_graph.ado
f _littext_example.ado
*
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
* Python pipeline. Filenames are case-sensitive; preserve forward
* slashes in the path so net install creates the python/ subdirectory
* correctly on all platforms.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
f python/__init__.py
f python/littext_env.py
f python/littext_pipeline.py
f python/littext_extract.py
f python/littext_embed.py
f python/littext_cluster.py
f python/littext_relate.py
f python/littext_io.py
f python/littext_state.py
f python/littext_viz.py
f python/littext_run.py
*
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
* Documentation files installed alongside the package.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
f README.md
f CHANGELOG.md
f CITATION.cff
